Indian officials said 200 people were injured in the quake. Dharan was hardest hit. Sunday's pre-dawn quake struck near the India-Nepal border. Police bulldozed unstable brick and mud houses today while those left homeless by an earthquake that killed at least 749 people sought shelter and awaited government aid. We will continue to demolish houses until we are satisfied (the ones remaining) are safe to live in, he said. We have no tent. Most of the homeless have moved in with neighbors or found shelter in tents erected on the soggy earth. Police Inspector G. 